=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: React mono-Boc-1,4-diaminobutane, BocNH(CH2)4NH2, with 3,4-dichlorobenzenesulfonyl chloride (base, e.g. Et3N) to give BocNH(CH2)4NHSO2C6H3Cl2 | Step 2: Remove Boc (TFA/CH2Cl2 or HCl/dioxane) to obtain H2N(CH2)4NHSO2C6H3Cl2 | Step 3: Open enantioenriched glycidyl methyl ether of the required configuration with this primary amine to form the chiral amino alcohol HO-CH(CH2OMe)-CH2NH(CH2)4NHSO2C6H3Cl2, installing the target stereocenter | Step 4: Convert the newly formed secondary amine to the isopropyl urea by reaction with isopropyl isocyanate, giving HO-CH(CH2OMe)-CH2N((CH2)4NHSO2C6H3Cl2)C(O)NHCH(CH3)2 | Step 5: Carbamylate the remaining alcohol with phenyl isocyanate to furnish COC[C@@H](CN(CCCCNS(=O)(=O)c1ccc(Cl)cc1Cl)C(=O)NC(C)C)OC(=O)Nc1ccccc1.

